The paper deals with the performance analysis of subspace-based parameter estimation schemes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of structured least squares (SLS) also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of optimization and control (cs.SI). Finally, the use of tensor-based ESPRIT algorithms may also make the paper relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
